column5: Went out to a nearby trib this morning by myself for a few hours.  There was a large amount of people in the area I usually start at, so I immediately went up stream to try my luck/test the waters.  Water was very low and clear, but I guess I did alright, went 4/4, and hooked into a few salmon.  Can't wait for some heavy rain/more fish.  Anyways here's a few pictures.  Crappy phone camera,   I really need a proper camera.  Cheers.
nice fish, good on ya  wise pinners don't set their reels down in sand
Nice fish!  Although they'd do better if you didn't let them flop around in the mud/sand.
nice steelies  i gotta catch one this fall!!
Thanks! I'll definitely keep that in mind/avoid it next time I get out.
Those are awesome. Good outing i would say
Nice fish! What about the guys who put their pins in the water while taking pictures with the fish? That can't be good either? That could be another topic later.
Rocheleauc,  Nice fish man.  It always pays when you do a little bit of leg work!  -Sawyer
nice looks like a good time
